definition: victory/success/to beat/to defeat/to surpass/victorious/superior to/to get the better of/better than/surpassing/superb (of vista)/beautiful (scenery)/wonderful (view)/(Taiwan pr. [sheng1]) able to bear/equal to (a task)
see 優勝劣汰|优胜劣汰[you1 sheng4 lie4 tai4]

sentences.english: The lucky winner enjoys his choice of wives and lovers.
sentences.chinese: 幸運的優勝者可以有權選擇不止一位妻子和愛人。

sentences.english: Spain’s World Cup-winning club contained seven Barcelona first-teamers.
sentences.chinese: 西班牙世界盃優勝俱樂部已有七名巴塞的首席隊員。

sentences.english: The winner will be consigned with the contract of entire design process.
sentences.chinese: 優勝方案的第一名將獲得本項目的全程設計委託合同。

sentences.english: The mayor distributed the prizes among the winners.
sentences.chinese: 市長給優勝者頒發獎品。

sentences.english: If time and scheduling permits, we may also visit Yosemite National Park or Lake Tahoe.
sentences.chinese: 如果時間允許可安排遊覽優勝美地或他後湖。

sentences.english: It is survival of the fittest, may great music win.
sentences.chinese: 這是優勝劣汰，願偉大的音樂得勝。

sentences.english: A decorative cup-shaped vessel awarded AS a prize or trophy.
sentences.chinese: 一種作爲獎品或優勝紀念品的裝飾性杯狀器皿。

sentences.english: Fans began lining up early in the morning to buy their cup - tie tickets.
sentences.chinese: 球迷大清早就開始排隊，等着買優勝杯決賽的入場券。

sentences.english: But prize winners will be informed by letter.
sentences.chinese: 但是，優勝者將專函通知。

sentences.english: It's up to you to make sure you and your horse become a winning team .
sentences.chinese: 它的成立給你，以確保您和您的馬成爲優勝隊伍。

sentences.english: The loser congratulated the winner of the race.
sentences.chinese: 輸者向比賽的優勝者祝賀。

sentences.english: She says the forty finalists represented excellence across many areas of science.
sentences.chinese: 她說，這40名入圍者代表着衆多科學領域的優勝者。

sentences.english: Liverpool were in a jubilant mood after their cup victory.
sentences.chinese: 利物浦隊奪得優勝杯後喜氣洋洋。

sentences.english: Fortunately, industry changes in recent years, the phenomenon of survival of the fittest is taking place.
sentences.chinese: 還好近幾年行業在變革，優勝劣汰的的現象正在發生。

sentences.english: Liverpool is in a jubilant mood after their cup victory.
sentences.chinese: 利物浦隊奪得優勝杯後喜氣洋洋。
